				<div class="RP"><br><ul><li>The ﬂhD operon regulatory region is a direct target for several regulatory proteins : These are the cyclic AMP-catabo-lite gene activator protein complex , which is an activator in response to an alleviation of catabolite repression ( 60 ) ; OmpR P , which represses at high osmolarity ( 57 ) ; histonelike nucleoid-structuring ( H-NS ) protein , an activator ( 5 , 60 ) ; LrhA , a repressor ( 27 ) ; RcsAB , a repressor ( 17 ) ; and HdfR , a repressor ( 23 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15516564" target="_blank">15516564</a>]<br></li>
