<li>Since LrhA is 95 % similar to PecT in the ﬁrst 120 amino acids , which contain the putative DNA-binding domain , and since lrhA49 : : cam phenocopies lrhA overexpression , we infer that LrhA functions as a DNA-binding protein that negatively autoregulates its own expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9882671" target="_blank">9882671</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since only one copy of IriiA was present , it has to be concluded that IrhA and LrhA are not essential under fhe conditions tested and do not significantly affect nuo expression and respiratory ( i.e. NADH oxidation-dependent ) growth .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7565112" target="_blank">7565112</a>]<br></li>
<li>Similar to ScoR ( GlgS ) , LrhA represses the expression of type 1 ﬁmbrial adhesins and ﬂagellar motility and chemotaxis genes [ 34,70 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23537328" target="_blank">23537328</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , increased expression of these genes after adaptation to acetate is not dependent on regulation by LrhA , and it remains to be shown how this regulation is mediated .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12620868" target="_blank">12620868</a>]<br></li>
<li>We expect that increased expression of chemotaxis and ﬂagellum genes after adaptation to propionate similarly is not dependent on regulation by LrhA , although we did not test this notion .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12620868" target="_blank">12620868</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of lrhA is subject to autoregulation , which could be important for the control of LrhA function .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>When a plasmid carrying the cloned lrhA gene was introduced into the wild type to increase the concentration of LrhA , the expression of lrhA cents -- cents lacZ increased and exceeded that of the lrhA mutant by a factor of 7.4 , suggesting that lrhA expression is under positive autoregulation by LrhA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>The response of lrhA expression to the presence of LrhA was tested using a lrhA cents -- cents lacZ gene fusion in lrhA-positive and - negative backgrounds ( Table 2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>The lrhA gene was under positive autoregulation by LrhA as shown by gel retardation and lrhA expression studies .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition autoregulation of lrhA expression by LrhA is indicated .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is suggested that LrhA affects this hierarchy at the top level by controlling the expression of ﬂhDC ( Fig. 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulators that affect ﬂhDC expression by controlling ﬂhDC transcription ( LrhA , OmpR-P , H-NS , cAMP/CAP ) or mRNA stability and translation ( CsrA ) positively ( + ) or negatively ( -- ) are shown .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123461" target="_blank">12123461</a>]<br></li>
<li>Similarly ﬁmB9 -- 9lacZ expression was not affected by LrhA , whereas the expression of ﬁmE9 -- 9lacZ was decreased about 2 ?	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16207912" target="_blank">16207912</a>]<br></li>
<li>Activation of ﬁmE expression by LrhA leads to repression of expression of the ﬁmA operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16207912" target="_blank">16207912</a>]<br></li>
<li>LrhA also controls its own expression , but unlike most LysRtype regulators , LrhA is positively autoregulated ( Lehnen et al. , 2002 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16207912" target="_blank">16207912</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results led us to propose a model ( Fig. 4 ) in which LrhA positively controls the expression of ﬁmE , as demonstrated by lacZ fusion and quantitative RT-PCR .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16207912" target="_blank">16207912</a>]<br></li>
